# MIGRATE-CLJ

Rails-like database migrations for Clojure.

## Installation

Via Clojars: http://clojars.org/migrate-clj

## Usage

(use 'migrate.core)
(require '[clojure.contrib.sql :as sql])

(defmigration "2010-11-01 21:30:10"
 "Create continent table."
 (sql/create-table
  "continents"
  [:id :text "PRIMARY KEY"])
 (sql/drop-table :continents))

(defmigration "2010-11-01 21:32:45"
 "Create country table."
 (sql/create-table
  "countries"
  [:id :text "PRIMARY KEY"]
  [:continent_id :text])
 (sql/drop-table :continents))

(sql/with-connection
 {:classname "org.sqlite.JDBC"
  :subprotocol "sqlite"
  :subname "db/test.sqlite3"
  :create true}
 (run))

